[ctns_make id='LF-InterceptInterceptFormS']

    [ctns_front]
Slope-Intercept Form<br>Linear Function
    [/ctns_front]

    [ctns_back style='width:80%;font-size:90%;']
The <strong>Intercept-Intercept Form</strong> of a linear function is given by the equation,
$|\frac{x}{A}+\frac{y}{B}=1,|$
for all $$x,y \in \mathbb{R}$$ and where $$A$$ and $$B$$ are constants, $$A,B \neq 0$$.
    [/ctns_back]

[/ctns_make]
